TopicTitle: B9 Aerospace doesnt load all the parts

Articles.Content:
KSP: 0.25 Windows 32-bit

Problem: When KSP is loading it doesnt loads some B9 aerospace parts.

Mods installed:

B9 Aerospace v. 5.2.6

IXS Interstelar Lite v. 1.0

Kerbal Attachment System v. 0.4.9

Reproduction steps:

I install the B9 Aerospace and then the other mods, then when I try to open KSP, It doenst load some parts of B9 Aerospace.

KSP log
Do you have the module manager dll installed?

@Kinryu:

Yes, s/he has Module Manager 2.5.1 installed and in the proper location. With any decent programmer's text editor, you can run a grep/regex search for dll$ in a KSP.log or output log to find all installed plugins.

@LightingStorm01:

Welcome to the forums, and thanks for (mostly) following the How to Get Support sticky.

Usually, we want the output log (KSP\KSP_Data\output_log.txt) rather than the KSP.log, since it provides much more information.

Have you tried starting a new sandbox save? I see over 200 B9 parts loaded.
